            <Title>why Shakespeare</Title>
            <Text>Examining network graphs requires, first, a substantial body of network graphs. Many scholars have handmade these graphs, either wholly by hand or as networks which can then be in Gephi. We developed a scalable method that minimizes reduplication of effort by building upon scholarly work to encode other features of plays through the Text Encoding Initiative standards.
Our TEI parser makes a number of simplifying assumptions in order to generate its network graphs of shared speech. 


We replicate some past results in order to verify our model, and then expand from there</Text>
